Deon Meyer's latest book has finally been translated into English. JOHANNESBURG - He's been described as the king of South African crime fiction, a doyen of the genre. And Deon Meyer is not just popular here. His Benny Griessel books are some of our best exports. Meyer's latest book has finally been translated into English. It's called The Last Hunt. The book centres around the body of a former policeman which was found close to a railway line. Griesel and his partner Vaugn Cupido race against time to solve the crime. Meyer spoke to Andrea van Wyk about The Last Hunt, his series Trackers and the Karoo.